   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>The role of the logged-in user should be <uicontrol>Fund Manager</uicontrol>. </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>
         <p>You can activate an inactive <uicontrol>Global Fund List</uicontrol> record to enable
            access for project fund usage.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>. </p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Enterprise Dashboard</uicontrol> is
               displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand the <uicontrol>Fund Management </uicontrol> folder, and then
               click <uicontrol>Global Fund
               List</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>GLOBAL FUND LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the list page, select the appropriate record to
               activate.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To activate a record, perform either of the
               following:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>
                     <p>In the toolbar, click <uicontrol>Mark Active/Inactive</uicontrol>, and
                        then click <uicontrol>Mark
                           Active</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p>In the toolbar, click <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>, select the
                           <uicontrol>Is Active</uicontrol> check
                        box, and then click <uicontrol>Save &amp;
                           Exit</uicontrol>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
            <p>The selected record is marked as
               active.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
